,Recommended,410340,19188204,"Posted: 21 November, 2015",all,wheels_up,"Really enjoying the game so far! I fly quads already but I'm trying to learn how to fly more aggressive racer quads. This game is helping me learn to fly with the tilted camera and with more power than I'm used to. The devs are very quick to fix any kind of problems and have improved the physics much since launch.The physics overall feel pretty solid. It would be nice to see some wind or other factors that make the quad feel a little less on rails. It's not bad at all, though. Flying in the game feels pretty similar to real life.I'm using the Taranis controller. Quick note: the game doesn't take negative inputs from the taranis, so make a new model, modify the curves to only be 50, and offset by 50. This means your left roll, for example, is really at what is normally the centerpoint (0) and your right roll is what is normally full right (100). You'll have to do this for all channels. In the guides section there's pre-made model files."
