76561198036897676,Recommended,410340,32972514,Posted: 28 June,all,Angry Monkeyz,"Not everyday is a good day to fly. It's raining outside, you're sick, you've been drinking, or you need to rebuild your favorite quad? No worries, fire up Liftoff, have a seat, and get ready to rip. Most pilots will tell you that you need to keep flying to keep your skills up, or you'll go rusty, and have to relearn everything all over again. It's about muscle memmory, timing, and familiarity. Liftoff helps out when you don't have any packs left to rip, or the weather isn't cooperating. Customize your quad as close as you can to the one yu fly with the workbench, tune it up in the ingame BetaFlight simulator, and set your FPV angle. Yhe FPV will also simulate the video noise you get from your headset from flying near large metal structures, behind trees, and distance (to a degree, you'll never lose Video like in real life).  Want to race it up with the community? Get out there and try the prebuilt tracks, or get on the Steam workshop and try out maps that others out there made. Loads of fun without the cost of crashed quads, busted props, and puffed packs.  Grab it and you'll be pleased. I have FrSky Taranis and Turnigy Evolution, and I have to say, the Evolution just worked as soon as I plugged her in, whereas the Taranis required me to make a model. Either way, easy set up and get to ripping.  Only downfall is the music tracks get really repetative, so fire up your own music. God mode in races isn't infalible but it really gives an edge to the guys that play with it always on, and will make you wonder how they slam the shipping container and still keep flying. This is solved by disabling god mode in any race you create, but don't expect the races you join to have it disabled. Well worth my hard earned money, since it makes me a better pilot without the cost of repair."
76561198178292507,Recommended,410340,33706267,Posted: 21 July,all,sheradenkirkham,"This simulator is fantastic! The best I've ever used. I tried the more popular $5 simulator thats out there, as well as the DRL sim and was disappointed in how little they helped my piloting skills. Liftoff is worth every penny and took me from a newbie pilot barely able to fly in Horizon mode to a full acro pilot. The fact that you have the ability to build a virtual drone with all the flight characteristics of your actual drone is a huge advantage in learning as how you fly in the simulator can almost directly transfer to real world flight. It feels really good and is astonishingly close to real world flight. And to top all of this off, you can actually tune your PID's. There is no finer simulator out there, nothing else even comes close!"
